                        <interp inst="t18641212-96-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>.—<hi rend="italic">He was further charged with having been before convicted of uttering, at this Court, in July</hi>, 1860, <hi rend="italic">in the name of <persName id="t18641212-name-68">
                        <interp inst="t18641212-name-68" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18641212-name-68" type="surname" value="ROBERTS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18641212-name-68" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>George Roberts, other-wise <rs id="t18641212-alias-2" type="alias">
                           <join result="nameAlias" targOrder="Y" targets="t18641212-name-68 t18641212-alias-2"></join>Smith</rs>
                     </persName>, sentence eighteen months: to which he</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
PLEADED GUILTY</hi>.—<hi rend="italic">
